## Legal Entity Structure

### Recommended: Holding Company Model

Based on research ([Source](https://bizee.com/articles/series-llc-holding-company-multiple-businesses)), the recommended structure is a traditional holding company with separate operating LLCs:

```
┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐
│                    KIKMAN ENTERPRISES LLC                    │
│                    (Holding Company - WY)                    │
│                                                              │
│  • Owns equity in all subsidiaries                          │
│  • Makes strategic decisions                                 │
│  • Holds IP, trademarks, domains                            │
│  • No direct operations or sales                            │
└─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘
                              │
          ┌───────────────────┼───────────────────┐
          │                   │                   │
          ▼                   ▼                   ▼
┌─────────────────┐  ┌─────────────────┐  ┌─────────────────┐
│  LAZYGOLF LLC   │  │ RENT-A-NERD LLC │  │   FUTURE LLC    │
│   (Operating)   │  │   (Operating)   │  │   (Operating)   │
│                 │  │                 │  │                 │
│ • Apparel sales │  │ • Caddy service │  │ • TBD ventures  │
│ • Platform ops  │  │ • Tech support  │  │                 │
│ • Content/media │  │ • Golf partners │  │                 │
└─────────────────┘  └─────────────────┘  └─────────────────┘
                              │
                              │ (Affiliate)
                              ▼
                    ┌─────────────────┐
                    │ NDEV CONSULTING │
                    │ (Travis's solo) │
                    │                 │
                    │ • IT consulting │
                    │ • Dev services  │
                    └─────────────────┘
```

### Why NOT Series LLC?

While Series LLCs are cheaper to maintain, they have limitations ([Source](https://www.kubera.com/blog/series-llc-vs-holding-company)):
- Only available in ~14 states
- Less understood by banks/investors
- Some states don't recognize series liability protection
- Can complicate fundraising

### State of Incorporation Analysis

Based on 2025 research ([Source](https://clemta.com/blog/wyoming-or-delaware-best-state-to-register-your-business-2025/)):

| Factor | Delaware | Wyoming | Home State (MN?) |
|--------|----------|---------|------------------|
| **Filing Fee** | $90 | $100 | Varies (~$155 MN) |
| **Annual Fee** | $300/yr franchise tax | $60/yr | Varies |
| **Privacy** | Moderate | **Best** (no disclosure) | Public |
| **Legal Framework** | **Best** (Court of Chancery) | Good | Standard |
| **VC Preference** | **Required** for VC | Acceptable | Less preferred |
| **Simplicity** | Complex | **Best** | **Best** |
| **"Dexit" Trend** | Companies leaving | Gaining popularity | N/A |

#### Recommendation

**Wyoming LLC for Kikman Enterprises** is the best choice because:
1. **No state income tax** - Tax savings on pass-through income
2. **Strong privacy** - No member disclosure required
3. **Lowest ongoing costs** - $60/year vs $300+ elsewhere
4. **Asset protection** - Strongest charging order protection
5. **No VC plans (initially)** - Delaware only matters if raising institutional capital

If LazyGolf later needs VC funding, can convert to Delaware C-Corp at that time.

