## Financial Infrastructure

### Business Banking

Recommended for holding company + subsidiaries ([Source](https://www.nerdwallet.com/p/best/small-business/banks-for-startups)):

| Bank | Type | Best For | Monthly Fee | Key Features |
|------|------|----------|-------------|--------------|
| **Mercury** | Online | Startups, tech companies | $0 | Up to $5M FDIC, expense management, great UX |
| **Bluevine** | Online | General small business | $0 | No fees, interest on balance |
| **Rho** | Online | Growing companies | $0 | Treasury management, bill pay automation |
| **Chase** | Traditional | Established businesses | $15 (waivable) | Credit building, physical locations, integrations |

#### Recommendation

**Mercury** for Kikman Enterprises because:
- Zero fees
- Modern API/integrations
- Startup-focused features
- Up to $5M FDIC insurance
- Clean expense tracking

**Structure:**
- Kikman Enterprises LLC → Mercury account (holding)
- LazyGolf LLC → Mercury account (operating)
- Keep accounts separate to maintain liability protection

### Accounting Software

Comparison ([Source](https://mercury.com/blog/best-accounting-software-startups-2025)):

| Software | Monthly Cost | Best For | Key Features |
|----------|-------------|----------|--------------|
| **Wave** | Free | Bootstrapped startups | Invoicing, expense tracking, basic reports |
| **QuickBooks** | $37-137/mo | Scaling businesses | 80+ reports, 650+ integrations, payroll |
| **FreshBooks** | $19-60/mo | Service businesses | Time tracking, project management, invoicing |
| **Xero** | $15-78/mo | Growing companies | Multi-currency, good integrations |

#### Recommendation

**Start with Wave (Free)** because:
- Zero cost while pre-revenue
- Full double-entry bookkeeping
- Invoicing included
- Bank feed integration
- Can export/migrate to QuickBooks later when scaling

**Upgrade to QuickBooks** when:
- Revenue exceeds $50K/year
- Need payroll
- Need inventory tracking (apparel)
- Need advanced reporting

### Tax Structure

| Entity Type | Tax Treatment | Best For |
|-------------|---------------|----------|
| **LLC (default)** | Pass-through (Schedule C or K-1) | Early stage, losses expected |
| **LLC taxed as S-Corp** | Salary + distributions | Profit >$40K, save self-employment tax |
| **C-Corp** | Corporate tax + dividends | VC funding, going public |

**Recommendation:** Stay as LLC with pass-through taxation initially. Consider S-Corp election when profitable and paying >$40K in self-employment tax annually.

